    ns1:description "Complete ChIP-seq analysis for single-end sequencing data. Processes raw FASTQ files through adapter removal (fastp), alignment to reference genome (Bowtie2), and quality filtering (MAPQ greater than 30). Peak calling with MACS2 uses a fixed extension of 200bp to identify protein-DNA binding sites. Generates alignment files, coverage, peak calls, and quality metrics for downstream analysis." ;
