    ns1:description """RNAseq workflow UMG: Here we introduce a scientific workflow implementing several open-source software executed by Galaxy parallel scripting language in an high-performance computing environment. We have applied the workflow to a single-cardiomyocyte RNA-seq data retrieved from Gene Expression Omnibus database. The workflow allows for the analysis (alignment, QC, sort and count reads, statistics generation) of raw RNA-seq data and seamless integration of differential expression results into a configurable script code.
""" ;
