    ns1:description """The ultimate-level complexity workflow is one among a collection of workflows designed to address tasks up to CTF estimation. In addition to the functionalities provided by layer 0 and 1 workflows, this workflow aims to enhance the quality of both **acquisition images** and **processing**.

**Quality control protocols**

…

**Combination of methods**
* **CTF consensus**
	* New methods to compare ctf estimations
	* CTF xmipp criteria (richer parameters i.e. ice detection)

**Advantages**:&nbsp;
* Control of the acquisition quality
* Robust estimations to continue with the processing""" ;
