    ns1:dateModified "2026-02-11T19:40:17Z"^^ns1:Date ;
    ns1:description "The workflow takes a (trimmed) Long reads collection, runs Meryl to create a K-mer database, Genomescope2 to estimate genome properties and Smudgeplot to estimate ploidy (optional). The main results are K-mer database and genome profiling plots, tables, and values useful for downstream analysis. Default K-mer length and ploidy for Genomescope are 31 and 2, respectively. " ;
    ns1:image <https://workflowhub.eu/workflows/2426/diagram?version=2> ;
    ns1:input <https://workflowhub.eu/workflows/603#erga_profiling_long_reads_v2602__wf1_-inputs-Ploidy>,
        <https://workflowhub.eu/workflows/603#erga_profiling_long_reads_v2602__wf1_-inputs-Run%20Smudgeplot?>,
